# Kakeibo (Household Budget) Tool — Development Rules

## Scope

- Build and maintain **MoneyForward ME CSV ingestion, combining, marking, and
  month x person expense aggregation** only.
- Do not add budgeting advice, spending predictions, or investment logic.
- Keep this tool independent from the Parcel demo (`src/index3.js`) and the
  US market news tool (`src/news/**`).

## Privacy (critical)

- This is personal financial data. **Never commit real MoneyForward export
  CSVs, combined ledgers, or exported mark files to the repository.**
- `data/` is gitignored for exactly this reason — keep it that way.
- **Supabase off (default build):** no network calls; localStorage only.
- **Supabase on (env configured):** ledger data syncs to Supabase Postgres
  after Magic Link login. All access must go through **RLS policies** in
  `supabase/migrations/` — never expose the service_role key in the frontend
  or GitHub Actions build secrets (anon key only).
- Cloud sync lives in `supabaseSync.js` / `transactionDb.js`; keep core
  parse/aggregate modules network-free so they remain unit-testable in Node.
- Tests and fixtures must use fabricated/anonymized data only, never real
  names, real account names, or real amounts from an actual export.
- Do not log full transaction contents (merchant names, memos) to the
  console in production code paths; status/error logs should stay limited to
  counts and non-sensitive metadata.

## Data model

- Core parsing/combining/aggregation logic (`csv.js`,
  `parseMoneyForwardCsv.js`, `combineTransactions.js`, `aggregate.js`,
  `ledgerCsv.js`) must stay framework-agnostic plain JS (no `fs`, no DOM) so
  it can run unchanged in both the Node CLI and the browser bundle.
- `ledgerCsv.js` is this tool's own round-trippable export format (carries
  marks alongside transaction data). Keep `buildLedgerCsv`/`parseLedgerCsv`
  in sync with each other and with `LEDGER_HEADER` — a browser reload must be
  able to fully restore state from a previously downloaded ledger CSV alone.
- Transaction identity is the MoneyForward `ID` column; dedupe, mark
  persistence, and memo-edit persistence must always key off of it. The ID
  is intentionally never rendered as a visible ledger table column, but it
  must always be captured on import and preserved on every export.
- The `メモ` (memo) column from MoneyForward exports is a real, editable
  field, not incidental metadata: it must be parsed in, shown/editable in
  the ledger table, preserved on ledger CSV export, and restored on
  reimport (both via the ledger CSV round-trip and via `memoOverrides.js`
  for the "reload the same raw MoneyForward CSV" case, which has no other
  way to remember an edit).
- Expense aggregation must exclude: income rows (amount >= 0), transfers
  (`振替` = 1), and rows excluded from MoneyForward's own calculation
  (`計算対象` = 0). Keep this logic centralized in
  `aggregate.js#isExpenseEligible`.
- The mark value set is `PERSON_ME` / `PERSON_SPOUSE` / `PERSON_SHARED` /
  `PERSON_EXCLUDED` (`MARK_KEYS` in `aggregate.js`). `PERSON_EXCLUDED`
  ("除外") is a manual override for money-movement-only transactions
  MoneyForward didn't flag as a transfer (e.g. a bank wire) — it must be
  dropped from every total (`totals`, `byMonth`, `unmarked`), tracked only
  in `excludedByMark` for transparency, and must never be added to
  `PERSON_KEYS` (which is specifically the set of columns shown in the
  money totals table).

## Testing

- Add/keep unit tests in `test/kakeibo/` for any change to parsing, combining
  or aggregation logic. Use `node --test`.
- Never add real personal CSVs as test fixtures; construct minimal inline
  CSV strings with made-up data instead.

## UI

- Keep the browser UI served via Parcel as a separate entry point
  (`kakeibo.html`), not merged into `index.html`. No React/Vue — plain JS.
- `@supabase/supabase-js` is the only allowed runtime dependency for cloud sync.

## Deployment (GitHub Pages)

- `.github/workflows/deploy-pages.yml` builds `index.html` and `kakeibo.html`
  as a static site and deploys it to GitHub Pages on push to `main`.
- Optional `SUPABASE_URL` / `SUPABASE_ANON_KEY` secrets are injected at build
  time. When empty, the app runs in localStorage-only mode.
- Keep the `--public-url` flag in the workflow in sync with the GitHub Pages
  project path (`/${{ github.event.repository.name }}/`) so built asset URLs
  resolve correctly under the project subpath.
- Do not add analytics or unrelated third-party scripts.

## Supabase

- Schema and RLS live in `supabase/migrations/` — apply via Supabase SQL Editor
  or CLI; document changes in `docs/supabase-setup.md`.
- Pattern B (full ledger in DB): `transactions` table stores all fields +
  mark + memo, keyed by `(household_id, moneyforward_id)`.
- Single-user model today; `households` / `household_members` tables are
  structured for future couple-sharing without breaking RLS.
